A vintage-style illustration showing a child's wooden school desk from the 1950s with old-fashioned notebooks and pencils, but casting a long shadow that transforms into the silhouette of a towering, ominous gateway or portal. The shadow stretches across a warm sepia-toned classroom floor with afternoon sunlight streaming through tall windows. The contrast between the innocent, nostalgic desk and its dark, imposing shadow creates tension. Muted browns, creams, and amber tones dominate, with the shadow rendered in deep indigo. The composition emphasizes the small scale of childhood against the looming digital world they're being pushed toward.
